-- Apple rolls out much-anticipated iPhone
-- 
-- Tue Jan 9, 2007 1:27pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/09/us-apple-macworld-iphone-idUSN0949313120070109

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Apple Computer Inc. Chief Executive Steve Jobs introduced an eagerly anticipated Apple-branded mobile phone with a touch-screen that combines features from the popular iPod music player. 

 Speaking at the company's Macworld conference on Tuesday, Jobs said the device would be called the iPhone. Jobs' speech was expected to continue until 11 a.m. local time (1900 GMT).